text.tspan: Share of the population with depression by average income of the country,
The prevalence of depressive disorders in a given population is measured as the age-standardized prevalence, which assumes
a constant age structure to compare between countries and through time. Figures attempt to provide a true estimate (going
beyond reported diagnosis) of depression prevalence based on medical, epidemiological data, surveys and meta-regression
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease
